         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">12 June 1889. ¶  ¶ Be so kind, dear Mr Holtze, to inform me of the colour of the fresh petals (the inner floral parts outside the filaments) of your  ¶ Pachynema ¶  species. ¶  ¶ Your orchid No. 862 ¶...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">89.06.12</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">To Maurice Holtze</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="de">GRG 19/391, State Records of South Australia, Adelaide.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">12</seg>
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">12 <seg style="font-style: italic; ">over</seg> 10.</p>
               </note>
               <seg style="">/6/89</seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Seien Sie so freundlich, lieber Herr Holtze, mir mitzutheilen, was frisch die Farbe der Petala (innere Blumentheile ausser halb der Staubfäden) von den <name key="Pachynema">Pachynema</name> Arten ist.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ihre Orchidee 862 ist — soweit ich ermittelt habe — eine Eulophia, u habe ich solche eben für den Vict. Naturalist beschrieben als E. Holtzei. Sie würden aber gut thun, wenn Sie einige </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">ungeöffnete</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> Blumen in starken Gin thäten, in ein kleines Gläschen, u nachdem die Blume einige Tage darin gelegen, den meisten Gin abgiessen, u dann das Gläschen in einem Kästchen durch die Post senden. Zerbräche es, dann könnte der wenige zurück gebliebene Gin oder Whiskey die andern Postsachen nicht beschädigen. Ich ersuche Sie </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">einstweilen</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> diese Orchidee </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">nicht</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> an Mr Ridley zu senden, denn es wäre möglich, dass sie eine <name key="Dipodium">Dipodium</name> wäre. Der Unterschied ist nur in der Anheftung der Pollen-Massen, u ich habe dies von den aufgeweichten Blumen Ihrer Exemplare nicht genau sehen können. </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>717 . R Br</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Habe ich Ihnen die neue Ausgabe der "Select plants" geschickt? Notizen für die nächste wären mir lieb.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Könnte gelegentlich ein Passagier mir eine Wurzel (feucht gehalten) von dem dortigen Bambus bringen? </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">Bestens grüssend</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">12 June 1889.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               </seg>Be so kind, dear Mr Holtze, to inform me of the colour of the fresh petals (the inner floral parts outside the filaments) of your <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Pachynema">Pachynema</name>
               </seg> species.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="">M had received specimens of </seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Pachynema">Pachynema</name>
                     </seg>
                     <seg style=""> on several occasions from 1882, but AVH</seg>
                     <seg style=""> lists none at MEL (searched as the current name </seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Hibbertia</seg>
                     <seg style="">) collected in 1889 (accessed 23 May 2022).</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Your orchid No. 862<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">A specimen was acknowledged in M to M. Holtze, 24 March 1889 (in this edition as 89-03-24a), but M may have had the species earlier; some specimens became mislaid and he requested replacements in M to M. Holtze, 26 January 1889 (<seg style="">in this edition as 89-01-26a)</seg>. <seg style="">MEL 108328 and MEL 108329, each bearing Holtze's collecting number 862, are dated '1888' by M on his labels; MEL 108309, also with Holtze's number 862, is labelled by M as '1889' (although the AVH record dates it to 1888 (accessed 23 May 2022))</seg>.</p>
               </note> is — as far as I was able to determine — a <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Eulophia</seg>, and I have just described it for the <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Victorian naturalist</seg> as <seg style="font-style: italic; ">E. holtzei</seg>.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">B89.07.03, p.55.</p>
               </note> But you would do well to place a few <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">unopened</hi>
               </seg> flowers in strong gin in a small glass and, after the flowers have been lying in it for a few days, pour off most of the gin, then place the little glass in a small box and send it through the mail. Should it break, the little remaining gin or whiskey would not damage the other postal articles. I ask that <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">for the time being</hi>
               </seg> you do <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">not</hi>
               </seg> send this orchid to Mr Ridley, because it is possible that it is a <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Dipodium">Dipodium</name>
               </seg>. The only difference is in the attachment of the pollen mass, and I was not able to see that properly in the soaked flowers of your specimens.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>717 <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Cheilanthes%20caudata">Cheilanthes caudata</name>
               </seg> R. Br.<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">O<seg style="">n an </seg>
                     <seg style="background-color: #ffff00; ">undated determination list, c. 1888,</seg>
                     <seg style=""> M had commented that collecting number 717 was probably a form of </seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Cheilanthes%20caudata">Cheilanthes caudata</name>
                     </seg>
                     <seg style=""> or </seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Pteris nudiuscula</seg>
                     <seg style=""> that was completely new to him</seg>.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Have I sent you the new edition of the <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Select plants</seg>?<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">B88.12.01.</p>
               </note> I would be pleased with notes for the next edition.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Could a passenger bring me a root (kept moist) of the bamboo from there, if the occasion presents itself?</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Best greetings</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Cheilanthes%20caudata">Cheilanthes caudata</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Dipodium">Dipodium</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Eulophia%20holtzei">Eulophia holtzei</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Pachynema">Pachynema</name>
            </p>
         </div>
      </body>
